task_description: Facing the building to your East (approx. 103°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: The top of the target building is not visible in the current view, so I need to tilt my head up to see the entire structure before I can estimate its height.
I have seen the middle and top of the building; now I need to look down to see its base to get a complete view for height estimation.

Having viewed the top, middle, and now the base of the building, I have a complete picture and can estimate its height by counting the floors; it appears to be about 8 stories high, and assuming a standard height of 3.5 meters per story including structure, the total height is approximately 28 meters.
